### Description

Add a virtual metod `OnApplyTemplate()` to `TemplateView` class, so that `TemplateView` derived classes (custom templated controls) know when when template was realized into a control in order to access inner children.

### API Changes
```
public class TemplatedView : ...
{
       ...
       protected virtual void OnApplyTemplate()
       {
            // this.FindName('_child') should work here
       }
}
```

### Intended Use Case

In Xamarin Forms, there's no simple\clean way to know when a custom control's `ControlTemplate` was applied so that the custom control can get access to its child controls. I'm not saying it's not possible, but there should be a method simple and elegant like in Windows XAML.

In Windows XAML, the `Control` class has an `OnApplyTemplate`: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/uwp/api/windows.ui.xaml.frameworkelement#Windows_UI_Xaml_FrameworkElement_OnApplyTemplate
